      • getOperatorDef

        IFProOperator[] getOperatorDef(long id,
                               int minPrty,
                               int maxPrty,
                               IFProOperator.OperatorType... types)

        Get operator definitions under the given condition. Returned set will be ordered by priority:

        • from min to max value, if minPrty < maxPrty
        • from max to min value, if minPrty > maxPrty
        Parameters:
        id - operator id to get definitions
        minPrty - min available operator priority. See remarks above
        maxPrty - max available operator priority. See remarks above
        types - operator types to select.
        Returns:
        operator declarations t\for the given condition
